<text top="1921" left="179" width="968" height="63" font="font5" id="p1_t33" reading_order_no="27" segment_no="2" tag_type="text">The  concept  of  affordance,  originally  developed  in  per- </text>
<text top="1974" left="180" width="967" height="62" font="font4" id="p1_t34" reading_order_no="28" segment_no="2" tag_type="text">ception  psychology  [2],  has  been  brought  into  comput- </text>
<text top="2026" left="180" width="967" height="62" font="font4" id="p1_t35" reading_order_no="29" segment_no="2" tag_type="text">ing  [5,  10].  An  affordance  is  an  action  possibility  that  is </text>
